data.productDescription:
4over’s sturdy, ultra thick, 32pt black edge business cards are modern, sleek, and undeniably impressive. This unique business card features a black-colored core fixed between two layers of bright white. 


Printed on premium uncoated face stock and in a wide variety of sizes, black edge business cards are perfect for bold high-impact branding.


Black Edge Business Card Uses


  • Real Estate
  • Law Professionals
  • Artist/Photographer
  • Retail
  • Travel Agent
  • Interior Design

faqs.answer: Black edge business cards are made of three premium quality stocks adhered together creating an ultra-thick, 32pt triple layered card with a colored core. Face Stock: 9pt bright white premium uncoated with a smooth finish. Insert Stock: 14pt premium opaque black.
faqs.question: What materials are used to make a black edge business card?

faqs.answer: Yes, black edge business cards are made of premium uncoated paper and are easily written on.
faqs.question: Can you write on black edge business cards?

faqs.answer: No. Black edge business cards are also offered with optional rounded corners.
faqs.question: Are square edges the only type of corners available for black edge business cards?

faqs.answer: Yes. You can choose between horizontal or vertical templates.
faqs.question: Can black edge business cards be printed horizontally or vertically?

faqs.answer: Black edge business cards are made to last for years under normal conditions. Cards exposed to exceedingly high temperatures will have undesirable results. For example, if one were to expose these cards to a very high heat for extended periods of time, like in the windshield of a car, the longevity of the cards will be compromised. Black edge business cards should not be exposed to excessive heat or cold, as well as excessively dry or humid environments.
